","Develop within the thymus","Unable to present antigens to T cells","Cannot differentiate into memory cells"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EB lymphocytes are crucial components of the adaptive immune system. \u003Cstrong\u003EB cells compose 20-30% of peripheral blood lymphocytes\u003C/strong\u003E, with T cells making up the remaining 70-80%.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrimarily target intracellular pathogens\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as B cells produce antibodies that target extracellular pathogens, while T cells handle intracellular threats. \u003Cstrong\u003EDevelop within the thymus\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect since B cells develop in the bone marrow, while T cells develop in the thymus. \u003Cstrong\u003EUnable to present antigens to T cells\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect because B cells can function as antigen-presenting cells. \u003Cstrong\u003ECannot differentiate into memory cells\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as B cells can differentiate into both plasma cells and memory B cells. B cells are essential for humoral immunity through antibody production, antigen presentation, and development of immunological memory.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["B lymphocytes develop in bone marrow and comprise 20-30% of peripheral blood lymphocytes.","B cells produce antibodies that target extracellular pathogens.","B cells can function as antigen-presenting cells to T cells.","B cells can differentiate into plasma cells and memory B cells for long-term immunity."],"references":["Bona, C. A., \u0026 Bonilla, F. A. (2019). Textbook of immunology. CRC press","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Janeway CA Jr, Travers P, Walport M, et al. Immunobiology: The Immune System in Health and Disease. 5th edition. New York: Garland Science; 2001. Chapter 9, The Humoral Immune Response. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK10752/","Hoffman W, Lakkis FG, Chalasani G. B Cells, Antibodies, and More. Clin J Am Soc Nephrol. 2016 Jan 7;11(1):137-54. doi: 10.2215/CJN.09430915. Epub 2015 Dec 23. PMID: 26700440; PMCID: PMC4702236."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97443"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14988"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97443","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97443"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-23T17:46:55+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-23T17:47:06+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7676"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115440"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4908","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4908"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Immunology","synonyms":[],"descrip